summary: Kierhes' Pointless and Grammatically Incorrect Hanash Number One.
body:
Kierhes’ Pointless and Grammatically Incorrect Hanash Number One.

I honestly feel like a special snowflake on my last year in college for I still have so many things on my long list of firsts that are yet to be crossed out–drinking liquor being one of them; something my friends, and practically everyone my age have already achieved. “Getting drunk” on their lists had already been crossed out with a sharpie a long time ago, ink smudged; their drunken state to blame.


I don’t know why people resort to alcohol everytime they have problems–or lack thereof. What’s so fun about drinking something that could potentially harm your organs? What’s so thrilling about hangovers? What’s so appealing about getting drunk?


Is it the late night conversations they crave? The druken words they want to hear and/speak that couldn’t be uttered when sober? Or maybe they just find pleasure in headaches that they’d get the following day. I never understood the reasoning behind it. But whatever it may be, me being an anti-social pessimist will surely never understand any of it for I’ve never experienced it first hand nor have I ever had any reason to get drunk. I’d rather stay home and make landi online whenever im stressed/despressed/happy than get wasted— unless it’s with THE Harry Styles, I will never get drunk, so I will basically stay sober forever. I shall never have alcohol in my system.


But that’s the thing isn’t it? We’re all different. We don’t have a universal way of coping and/ expressing emotions.


Some people drink to forget; to feel numb. Some do it for fun. Some do it to remember. And some choose to stay tf away from alcohol and be hydrated with water instead. And unless your drinking become an addiction and negatively affect the people around you, the way you want to cope with things is none of anyone’s business.


…


Walwal is cool. Alcohol is cool but have yall ever hugged harry styles? lmao yeah me neither, pass the Alfonso sis.

summary: Harry's hair has entered a difficult transitional stage. Your patience and kindness during the coming months will be...
body: Harry’s hair has entered a difficult transitional stage. Your patience and kindness during the coming months will be appreciated. Do not point, sneer, laugh uncontrollably or [note to self] make references to 17th century court minstrels. If this proves too difficult to resist, please avert your eyes until this phase has been successfully completed. Mockery may trigger a reactionary haircut and must be avoided at all cost. Thank you for your patience. The rewards will be heavenly.
